<p>

<b>Eveready Income Fund</b> (<exchange wordnetid="111409538" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../584/205584.xml">
TSX</link></exchange>
:&nbsp;<weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://cxa.marketwatch.com/TSX/en/Market/quote.aspx?symb=EIS.UN">
EIS.UN</weblink>), is a growth-oriented income fund headquartered in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../405/95405.xml">
Edmonton</link></village>
, <district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../717/717.xml">
Alberta</link></district>
 that operates in the industrial and oilfield services sectors of North American.</p>

<sec>
<st>
Profile</st>
<p>

<b>Eveready Income Fund</b> operates in Canada and the United States. They have a significant presence in the Fort McMurray oil sands through their Eveready Fort McMurray operation and in the Cold Lake oil sands through their Eveready Bonnyville operation. The company provides services to the oil and gas, forestry, mining, manufacturing, and power generation industries.</p>
<p>

<b>Evereaday Income Fund</b> is one of the fastest growing companies in Alberta.</p>
<p>

<b>Eveready Income Fund</b> services to these industries include industrial and oilfield services, health/safety and environmental services, and oilfield equipment rental services.  The company operates from over 40 locations in Canada, the United States, and worldwide.</p>

